item.title: Europe Chafes at Slow Pace of Covid-19 Vaccine Approval
item.description: The EU’s chief drug regulator is coming under pressure from some governments to authorize a Covid-19 vaccine designed and produced on EU soil, as the continent struggles to contain a wave of cases ahead of the Christmas period.

item.title: Putin Acknowledges Biden's Election Win for First Time
item.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin congratulated President-elect Joe Biden on his election win, but some senior Russian officials said they were doubtful that the coming change in the White House would improve relations.

item.title: China Economy Continues Recovery Despite Covid-19 Surge Elsewhere
item.description: China’s economic activity extended its momentum in November with an across-the-board recovery, putting the world’s second largest economy on stronger footing as it approaches the end of a tumultuous year.

item.title: U.S. Sanctions Iranian Intelligence Officers Over Abduction of Former FBI Agent
item.description: The action by the Treasury Department was the first public move to formally hold Iran accountable for the abduction of Robert Levinson, who went missing in 2007.

item.title: Oil Tanker Attacked at Saudi Port Amid Iran Tensions
item.description: A boat loaded with explosives attacked an oil tanker docked at the Saudi port city of Jeddah in what the authorities there called an act of terrorism, the latest in a string of strikes against the kingdom’s oil infrastructure in recent weeks.

item.title: U.S. Sanctions Turkish Entities Over Acquisition of Russian Defense System
item.description: The U.S. exerted new pressure on Turkey over its installation of a Russian air-defense system, the latest sign of a growing rift between Ankara and its allies in the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.

item.title: Rollout of Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 Vaccine Slows in U.K.
item.description: British doctors say distributing the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine for Covid-19 beyond hospitals will take longer than expected because of the need to monitor patients for allergic reactions after injection.
